Nice intro.  I&#39;ll recommend it to people looking for information.

An aside:

One of the responses to the article raised what seems to be a standard 
objection to REST-over-HTTP:  The &quot;parameters too big&quot; problem, wherein 
the number of parameters needed to specify a URI for a resource exceeds 
the practical limits of today&#39;s tools (*cough* IE). 

It seems to me that the standard response to this should be that if the 
amount of data needed for a query is that large and complicated, you 
might well want to represent it as a resource in its own right with its 
own (small) URI anyway.  Certainly the example I saw recently of an 
image search application, which requires an image as an examplar to base 
a search on, seems to fall into this category.  Is this a reasonable answer?

